frameDefinitions: The judge or other court officer (the Authority) informs the Accused of the Charges against him/her, i.e. the alleged actions and the relevant laws. '' 'The board has been accused by the federal court of making decisions based on narrow agendas and meddling where it shouldn't.'
A Speaker uses as a Label to refer to an Entity.
A Communicator communicates a judgment of an Evaluee to an Addressee.

Blend of Rewards_and_punishments and Bodily_injury in which the Agent performs some action intended to cause Bodily harm to the Evaluee as a consequence of some action or belief of the Evaluee (the Reason).

This frame covers a step in a criminal process in which a  Judge decides whether the Accused should be released on bail, and, if so, what the amount of the bail should be.  '' 'Thorsen, of Grimstad, Norway, was granted $100,000 bail until June 18.'
frameExamples: The board has been <t>accused</t> by the federal court of making decisions based on narrow agendas and meddling where it shouldn't.
I <t>commended</t> his handling of the crisis.
The Sheriff <t>flogged</t> him for his crimes.

listRoleDefinitions: The judge or other authority of the court in which the accused person is arraigned.
The person being charged with an offense against the law.
The crime with which the Accused is charged
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The <fen>Speaker</fen> is the person who conventionally uses a linguistic sign to refer to an <fen>Entity</fen>.
The concrete or abstract thing with which the <fen>Speaker</fen> has associated a particular linguistic sign.
The linguistic sign that the <fen>Speaker</fen> uses to designate the <fen>Entity</fen>.
A text whose author applies a particular <fen>Label</fen> to an <fen>Entity</fen>.
A time period in which a <fen>Speaker</fen> uses the <fen>Label</fen>.
A physical space whose occupants use the <fen>Label</fen> to refer to the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Communicator</fen> uses language in the written or spoken modality to convey his or her evaluation of the <fen>Evaluee</fen> to another person.
<fen>Medium</fen> identifies the physical or abstract setting in which the evaluation is conveyed.
<fen>Topic</fen> identifies the entity to which the proposition or propositions conveyed relate.
A judgment is made about the <fen>Evaluee</fen>  With verbs this role is typically expressed as Object:
<fen>Expressor</fen> is the body part or action by a body part that conveys the judgment made by the <fen>Communicator</fen>.
Typically, there is a constituent expressing the <t>Reason</t> for the <fen>Communicator</fen>'s judgment. It is usually a <ment>for</ment>-PP.
When the communication of the judgment takes place.
Where the communication of the judgment takes place.
The Agent is the person performing the intentional act.
Evaluee is the person or thing about whom/which a judgment is made. With verbs this role is typically expressed as Object:

Where the event takes place.
At the time of bail setting, the <fen>Accused</fen> is held without bail/bond, released on his/her own recognizance, or required to give the Court  a specific amount of money for bail.
The <fen>Judge</fen>, as head of  the Court, determines the <fen>Accused</fen>'s bail.
<fen>Status</fen> idenitifies the decision made with regard to bail.  The possible statuses are 'without bail/bond', 'on one's own recognizance', or a specific amount of money required for bail.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the bail setting occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the bail setting occurs.
